extends java.lang.Object
    This class holds mashup metadata information for an application. Mashup helper keeps different instances of this class for each application. asmishra

        public java.lang.String loadMashupExtensions(org.w3c.dom.Document inDoc,

                                             java.lang.String uiMode,
                                             boolean extensibilityMode,
                                             org.w3c.dom.Element originalMashupEl)
        This method loads mashup extensions from a given document. used for mashup extensions from CUF UI Mashup Editor. inDoc extnType uiMode extensibilityMode originalMashupEl passed when an extension is being resent after editing in UI to be updated. So this element contains original mashup element on which the updated extension is applied.Used only for Incremental Extension.

      • loadMashupMetaData

        public void loadMashupMetaData(org.w3c.dom.Element mashupDefn,
                               java.lang.String overrideExisting)
        This method calls registerMashup. It is meant to be used only in wufdevmode. If application is not running in dev mode then this method gives an error. If overrideExisting is set to true, then the existing mashupMetaData is deleted form the map and the new mashupMetaData added by calling the registerMashup(Element) method. If overrideExisting is set as false it simply calls the registerMashup(Element) method. mashupDefn This method removes the specified mashupId from the mashupMetadataMap. If application is not running in dev mode then this method gives an exception. overrideExisting
